Average trail width: 8 feet;
Estimated average grade category: moderately steep (5-8%) with steeper sections at about 0.0 and 0.2 miles when going south;
Known barriers: stairs at about 0.4 miles.

This trail is an old railroad bed and is good for a relaxing walk in the wilderness. This is a wide, well-marked trail that works for hiking, cycling, cross-country skiing, or snowshoeing. Members report that it can be muddy.

According to Accessible Nature (https://www.accessiblenature.info/?page_id=157#federal): This trail is wheelchair-accessible with assistance over a wooden suspension bridge and along the west side of the Pemigewasset River. 

